      "writtenOn": "2016-06-27T18:00:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I do prefer the various window classes holding a pointer to EmulatorQtWindow and getting to other object from that \"context\".\nMost of our long-lived objects are owned by EmulatorQtWindow. Usually, you\u0027d have a Context object to hold such global data. In our case, it\u0027s simply EmulatorQtWindow.\n\nEmulatorQtWindow holds pointers to all objects that these sub-windows need, is the logical \"parent\" of these sub-windows, and is (or can be) guaranteed to outlive all these sub-windows.\n\nwdyt?",
      "parentUuid": "e3c531ce_56fa94c1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 28,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 28,
        "endChar": 43
      },
      "revId": "54aabb83936a03e8dad94221a1963cb9a0852a2c",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e3c531ce_d92b55dd",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/extended-pages/settings-page.h",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 28,
      "author": {
        "id": 1078773
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-06-27T18:07:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "DPadPage has a reason for doing it this way - it actually uses the interface exposed by EmulatorQtWindow (queueSkinEvent) that is related to what EmulatorQtWindow does.\n\nIn this case, however, we\u0027re adding a method that is completely unrelated to what EmulatorQtWindow actually does. I don\u0027t like it because EmulatorQtWindow is already pretty hairy (despite some efforts to reduce it) and we shouldn\u0027t be adding to the mess.\n\n\u003e  AdbInterface is a unique_ptr and should be kept that way\n\nI didn\u0027t propose making it not a unique_ptr. EmulatorQtWindow should still own AdbInterface, the other objects can use the raw pointer to refer to it.",
      "parentUuid": "e3c531ce_56fa94c1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 28,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 28,
        "endChar": 43
      },
      "revId": "54aabb83936a03e8dad94221a1963cb9a0852a2c",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e3c531ce_195b2d74",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/extended-pages/settings-page.h",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 28,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079748
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-06-27T18:11:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oh, I didn\u0027t see that birenbaum@ had added a function to EmulatorQtWindow for this.\nMy suggestion was to add an accessor to EmulatorQtWindow to get a raw pointer for AdbInterface.\nThe function to update the path belongs in AdbInterface, as Grigory requested.\n\nMy request is to treat EmulatorQtWindow like a context object for the sub-windows. So, instead of holding raw pointers to the various objects they might need to access that are owned by EmulatorQtWindow, they hold a raw pointer / weak pointer to EmulatorQtWindow, and use accessor methods to get hold of the objects themselves (here AdbInterface)",
      "parentUuid": "e3c531ce_d92b55dd",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 28,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 28,
        "endChar": 43
      },
      "revId": "54aabb83936a03e8dad94221a1963cb9a0852a2c",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e3c531ce_798341b7",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/extended-pages/settings-page.h",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 28,
      "author": {
        "id": 1078773
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-06-27T18:18:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t like it because it leads to bloating the interface of EmulatorQtWindow, making it responsible for stuff that it doesn\u0027t need to be responsible for.\n\nI think that, ideally, EmulatorQtWindow shouldn\u0027t even own these objects. It should do stuff related to presenting the window and responding to user events, while the \"global\" objects should be created in the correct order within a different \"context\", and injected as dependencies into constructors. But we have what we have, so let\u0027s at least try not to make it worse.",
      "parentUuid": "e3c531ce_b6ab0899",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 28,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 28,
        "endChar": 43
      },
      "revId": "54aabb83936a03e8dad94221a1963cb9a0852a2c",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e3c531ce_793181fb",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/extended-pages/settings-page.h",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 28,
      "author": {
        "id": 1078773
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-06-27T18:22:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That is closer to what I have in mind, but still not ideal IMO, because it smashes together two uinrelated concepts - \"main emulator window\" and \"container of global ui-related objects\".\nThat\u0027s a service locator pattern, I\u0027m proposing dependency injection.\nEven if we end up using a service locator, I\u0027d still prefer for it to be separate from EmulatorQtWindow.",
      "parentUuid": "e3c531ce_195b2d74",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 28,
